Map=(MapName="DH-HedgeHog_Push",Acronym=DH,PlayerCountMin=16,PlayerCountMax=32,FriendlyName=DH-HedgeHog_Push.LevelSummary.Title,Author="Tripwire",ScreenShot=DH-HedgeHog_Push.General.Hedge_preview,Description=DH-HedgeHog_Push.LevelSummary.Description,FallbackDesc="In late June 1944, the German Army Group Centre is facing a total collapse as the Soviets have launched a vast offensive against them. In some areas the German forces hold, in others they fall back. And in some they simply collapse. Those that can try to make an orderly retreat to something resembling safety to the west. Obviously, those with some transport fare best as they can stay ahead of the Soviet mobile forces.||In this map, a German rear-guard has to fight a delaying action against fast-charging Soviet pursuit. The Germans have a total of 3 sets of buildings to defend, spread across the map. The Soviet aim is to take them all.",FallbackName="'Hedgehog': Ukraine, 28th June 1944")